## CONCATATION
  it is used to join contents of two or more columns

->METHOD 1  :- using pipe operator  '||'

         synatx
         
         select (column1 || column2 || column3) as new_name
          from table_name
          
          -> METHOD 2 :- using concat() function
          
          syntax
          
          select concat(column1,column2,column3)
          from table_name
          
          
          
 ## DEFAULT
 
 it is used to give default value to the column
 
 syntax
 
 alter table table_name
add column new_column datatype  default 'give the default value' 





 
          
          
          
    
        
        
         
         
